    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Seems there is some demand to be able to access this statically.</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>How can I get such thing in static methods in non-spring-managed\n  classes? – Aetherus</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>It's a hack, but you can write your own class to expose it. You must be careful to ensure that nothing will call <code>SpringContext.getEnvironment()</code> before all beans have been created, since there is no guarantee when this component will be instantiated.</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Component\npublic class SpringContext\n{\n    private static Environment environment;\n\n    public SpringContext(Environment environment) {\n        SpringContext.environment = environment;\n    }\n\n    public static Environment getEnvironment() {\n        if (environment == null) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(\"Environment has not been set yet\");\n        }\n        return environment;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
